dialogue: Dogbert presents the seven advantages of being dumb.
There's a hole in the ozone layer.
Television is a source of constant wonder.
I wonder if Doogie is a doctor in real life.
You have a solution for every problem.
If people are starving in Africa they should move to France.
You are not constrained by a budget.
It was free! They just make you sign papers!
Instant replays are as exciting as live action.
This time he could make it.
You receive twice as many compliments.
You're kind of the Dan Quayle of dinosaurs.
